pageContext.claim: “WikiLeaks, et cetera, that's not my deal in life. You know, in other words, I don't know about WikiLeaks. It was a strange name. But there were stories about something WikiLeaks that they had information. And I say it in a joking manner at a speech. Joking. Everybody laughing. Everybody having a -- And they made it like it was serious.”
pageContext.analysis: There’s no indication that Trump was joking about wanting information or relying on information from WikiLeaks. He cited it regularly during the final weeks of the 2016 campaign.
